Essential geological phenomena and processes taking place inside the Earth and on the surface are discussed and introduced. Basic knowledge of the evolution of the Earth, origin of rocks, minerals and mineral resources is acquired.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Students will learn to recognize principal surficial and interior geodynamic processes, to identify minerals and rocks formed during these processes. They learn to describe Earth structure and periods of history.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students know the main endogenic and exogenic geological processes taking place on  the Earth, have a knowledge on the Earths  inner structure and the geological evolution of the Earth. Students have basic knowledge on the origin of main rock types and minerals, of main exogenic processes, sediment types and main landforms. Students acquire outlines of Estonian geology.
